l\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 07, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lov1718340866615.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lov1718340866615.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lov1718340866615.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wtq1665702660673\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Widget Reference: Forms and Reports\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__widget_referenceforms_and_reports_364442\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__p_d112079e1_d112080e1_d112081e1\">Report components support only non-editable EditBox and Picture widgets.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__p_d112082e1_d112083e1_d112084e1\">Uniface provides a set of physical widgets and a default set of logical widgets, which map to the physical widgets and set some of their properties.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__p_d112085e1_d112086e1_d112087e1\">Because most physical widgets have only one default logical widget, they are described in a single topic. When multiple logical widgets are mapped to a single physical widget, the physical and logical widgets are described individually.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__p_d112088e1_d112089e1_d112090e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kjk1665702557273.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjk1665702557273.html\" title=\"In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets.\">Widgets</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oir1665702612692.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oir1665702612692.html\" title=\"Use widgets in forms and reports to represent entities and fields and to control how users can use the data in those fields.\">Using Widgets in Forms and Reports</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widgets for Forms</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">Physical Widget (Logical Widget)</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\"> Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iic1718342502908.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iic1718342502908.html\" title=\"The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget.\">udefentity (Default Entity Widget )</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Represents the fields and occurrences of\n\t\t\t\t the entity as a multi-occurrence list. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clg1695282025414.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clg1695282025414.html\" title=\"The egrid widget displays data in a tabular format, in which the rows are occurrences of an entity and the columns are fields. It is an entity-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">egrid (Grid)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Represents the fields and occurrences of\n\t\t\t\t the entity within a grid framework, resembling a table. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fxi1688449052174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxi1688449052174.html\" title=\"The ucheckbox widget enables the user to set a Boolean value in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called CheckBox, which is mapped to ucheckbox.\">ucheckbox (CheckBox)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to select one of two or three previously\n                     defined values.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kzn1665703126224.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kzn1665703126224.html\" title=\"The ucolorbox widget displays a color value, either a color name or RGB value, in a color box in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called ColorBox, which is mapped to ucolorbox.\">ucolorbox (ColorBox)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to enter and display a standard color. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gzs1665702629046.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gzs1665702629046.html\" title=\"The (ucolorlist) widget displays a list of system or web colors for selection in a form component. Uniface provides a logical widget called ColorList, which is mapped to ucolorlist.\">ucolorlist (ColorList)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays a list of system or Web colors.\n\t\t\t\t </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmo1688449724415.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmo1688449724415.html\" title=\"The ucombobox widget combines an input field with a drop-down list. It allows users to select one item from a previously defined list, or enter their own data instead. It is applicable only to form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called ComboBox, which is mapped to ucombobox.\">ucombobox (Combo Box)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to select one item from a previously\n\t\t\t\t defined list, or enter user-defined data instead.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"3\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nnf1665702631473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nnf1665702631473.html\" title=\"The ucmdbutton widget is a button that the user can click to initiate an action. It is a field-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">ucmdbutton</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrc1665702631553.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrc1665702631553.html\" title=\"The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button.\">CommandButton</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Button that performs an action when\n\t\t\t\t clicked. By default, follows Windows look and feel.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gaf1665702631801.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gaf1665702631801.html\" title=\"The HeaderButton is a logical widget for styling a button to look like a column heading.\">HeaderButton</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Button styled as a Windows column header. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"soa1665702631628.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/soa1665702631628.html\" title=\"The UnifaceButton is a logical widget for a button that can be styled using colors and images. It supports properties that are not available for other command buttons.\">UnifaceButton</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Button that can be styled as desired using many properties unavailable with other logical button widgets. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sgr1665702633536.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sgr1665702633536.html\" title=\"The udragdrop widget is a control that accepts input from another uDragDrop, other Uniface applications, and from Microsoft Windows Explorer. It enables the user to transfer values or perform other actions by dragging an object from one widget and dropping it on another.\">udragdrop</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nyh1665702633605.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nyh1665702633605.html\" title=\"The DragSource logical widget is used to provide input for a drag-and drop action that transfers a value to a DropTarget widget. The data is transferred as a Uniface list.\">DragSource</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Source for drag and drop behavior.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wrn1665702633674.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wrn1665702633674.html\" title=\"The DropTarget logical widget accepts input dragged from a DragSource, other Uniface application, or Microsoft Windows Explorer. The data that is transferred consists of a Uniface list.\">DropTarget</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Target for drag and drop behavior. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fud1688450548955.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fud1688450548955.html\" title=\"The udropdownlist widget is a field-level widget that can display a list of valid options in a list below the input field, so that the user can select one. It is applicable only to form components.\">udropdownlist (DropDownList)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to select one value from a list of\n                     alternative choices.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"3\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sgr1665702639069.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sgr1665702639069.html\" title=\"The ueditbox widget is a field-level input control that enables the user to view and enter data in a field. It is applicable only to form components.\">ueditbox (EditBox)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"klb1688454363706.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/klb1688454363706.html\" title=\"Default logical widget for entering and displaying data in a field in a Form or Report.\">EditBox</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Input field used to enter, edit, and display text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">NoEditBox</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Edit box for styling a field that displays text but does not\n\t\t\t\t allow editing. For compatibly purposes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">Message Box</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Edit box for styling a field used to display a message. For compatibly purposes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gev1665702640020.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gev1665702640020.html\" title=\"The ucontainer widget embeds a non-modal form in a field of the current form. Uniface provides a logical widget called FormContainer, which is mapped to ucontainer.\">ucontainer (FormContainer)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to embed a form within another form.\n\t\t\t\t </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ied1665702642247.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ied1665702642247.html\" title=\"The uhtml widget is a field-level widget in a form component that renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page (when the field value is a URL prefixed by an ampersand (&amp;www.mysite.com/doc/index.html). Uniface provides a logical widget called HTML, which is mapped to uhtml.\">uhtml (HTML Widget)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hta1665703126401.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hta1665703126401.html\" title=\"The uhyperlink widget is a display-only widget that acts like a hyperlink in a web page. It activates a command when the user clicks it. It can only be used in form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called Hyperlink, which is mapped to uhyperlink.\">uhyperlink (Hyperlink)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Activates the detail trigger for the\n                     corresponding field.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">ulabel</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ngv1688454370143.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ngv1688454370143.html\" title=\"A label displays text on a component, such as the name of an associated field or an instruction to the user.\">Label</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays text on a component, such as the\n\t\t\t\t name of an associated field or an instruction to the user. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rez1688451198680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rez1688451198680.html\" title=\"The ulistbox widget is a field-level widget that displays an open list in which one or more values can be selected. It can only be used in form components.\">ulistbox (ListBox )</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays an open list in which one or more\n\t\t\t\t values can be selected.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gls1665702643795.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gls1665702643795.html\" title=\"The umap widget defines areas on an image that allow the user to interact by clicking on that area. It can only be used in form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called Map, which is mapped to umap.\">umap (Map)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Defines an area on an image that allows\n\t\t\t\t the user to interact by clicking on that area.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bwv1665702644903.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwv1665702644903.html\" title=\"The umeter widget displays the value of a Numeric field on a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values marked around the outer edge. Uniface provides a logical widget called Meter, which is mapped to umeter.\">umeter (Meter)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays the value of a field by\n\t\t\t\t representing the value as the hand of a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values\n\t\t\t\t marked around the outer edge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svk1665702646925.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svk1665702646925.html\" title=\"The umonthcalendar widget displays a month calendar to enable the user to select a date. Uniface provides a logical widget called MonthCalendar, which is mapped to umonthcalendar.\">(umonthcalendar) MonthCalendar</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays a calendar that allows the user\n\t\t\t\t to select a date.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vvo1665702647716.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vvo1665702647716.html\" title=\"The uOcxContainer widget embeds a Microsoft OCX control into a form component, and maps OCX properties and OCX events to fields and triggers. You can use ProcScript to activate OCX methods and let the OCX control activate widget triggers to respond to OCX events.\">uOcxContainer (OcxContainer)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Embeds OCXs in Uniface applications.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rdo1665702649920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rdo1665702649920.html\" title=\"The uOleContainer widget displays an embedded OLE object, enabling you to define links to OLE objects in Uniface applications.\">uOleContainer (OleContainer)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Embeds or defines links to OLE objects in\n\t\t\t\t Uniface applications.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ddd1665702643397.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ddd1665702643397.html\" title=\"The uoutputbox widget displays streaming text data. The data may come from a specified Output Channel, or be explicitly added. By default, it does not listen to any channel. Uniface provides a logical widget called OutputBox, which is mapped to uoutputbox.\">uoutputbox (OutputBox)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays streaming text data, including\n\t\t\t\t unicode-encoded data.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxc1665703126500.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxc1665703126500.html\" title=\"The upicture widget is used to displays the contents of an Image field. Uniface provides a logical widget called Picture, which is mapped to upicture.\">upicture (Picture)</a></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays an image.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qxp1665702650348.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qxp1665702650348.html\" title=\"The uprogressbar is a field-level widget the shows the progress of a process or action that is being executed. Is can only be used in form components. Uniface provides a logical widget called ProgressBar, which is mapped to uprogressbar.\">uprogressbar (ProgressBar)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Shows the progress of a process or action\n\t\t\t\t that is being executed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1665702650577.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1665702650577.html\" title=\"The uradiogroup widget displays a set of mutually exclusive choices as a group of radio buttons. Uniface provides a logical widget called RadioGroup, which is mapped to uradiogroup.\">uradiogroup (RadioGroup)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays values as a set of mutually\n\t\t\t\t exclusive choices, each of which is displayed as a radio button.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwk1688451210612.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwk1688451210612.html\" title=\"The urtfeditbox widget is used to display and edit text as Rich Text Format (RTF), which supports formatting such as font and color attributes, text alignment, indentation, and lists. Uniface provides a logical widget called RichEditBox, which is mapped to urtfeditbox.\">urtfeditbox (RichEditBox)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to edit and store, including font and\n\t\t\t\t color attributes, as rich text format (RTF).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"foe1665702651174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/foe1665702651174.html\" title=\"The uslider widget allows users to edit a numeric value in a field by sliding an indicator in a set of a previously defined range of values. Uniface provides a logical widget called Slider, which is mapped to uslider.\">uslider (Slider)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Used to enter or modify a value by sliding\n\t\t\t\t an indicator in a set of a previously defined range of values.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lxs1665702651483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lxs1665702651483.html\" title=\"The uspinbutton widget enables the user to enter or select a numeric value by clicking a button to increase or decrease a value by a predefined interval within a predefined range. Uniface provides a logical widget called SpinButton, which is mapped to uspinbutton.\">uspinbutton (SpinButton)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays a numeric value that can be\n\t\t\t\t increased or decreased by a predefined interval within a predefined range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bzj1665702641924.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzj1665702641924.html\" title=\"The utab widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tab, which is mapped to utab.\">utab (Tab)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays a tabbed container in which each\n\t\t\t\t tab contains a different form.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gyf1688451219719.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gyf1688451219719.html\" title=\"The utabex widget enables users to navigate through a collection of contained forms by clicking a tab to display the form. The utabex widget is highly customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs. Uniface provides a logical widget called TabEx, which is mapped to utabex.\">utabex (TabEx)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Displays a tabbed container in which each\n\t\t\t\t tab contains a different form. It is highly-customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gge1665702634237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gge1665702634237.html\" title=\"The utree widget enables users to view and navigate structured data as a hierarchy. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tree, which is mapped to utree.\">utree (Tree)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wtq1665702660673__table_d13268e1_d13269e1_d13270e1__entry__2\">Hierarchically represents data; used for\n                     navigation through structured data.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjk1665702557273.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Widgets</a><p>In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxl1704704845079.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Logical Widgets</a><p>Logical widgets are named configurations of physical widgets. A single physical widget may therefore have multiple logical widgets mapped to it. For fields, logical widgets provide the only way that physical widgets can be addressed.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uef1704698451038.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Properties for Styling the User Interface</a><p>Each object that can be viewed in the user interface has a collection of properties that can be used to control what it looks like, and some other aspects of its visual behavior.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7276295\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7276295\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Widget Reference: Forms and Reports Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 07, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Widget Reference: Forms and Reports Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows. Report components support only non-editable EditBox and Picture widgets. Uniface provides a set of physical widgets and a default set of logical widgets, which map to the physical widgets and set some of their properties. Because most physical widgets have only one default logical widget, they are described in a single topic. When multiple logical widgets are mapped to a single physical widget, the physical and logical widgets are described individually. For more information, see Widgets and Using Widgets in Forms and Reports . Table 1. Widgets for Forms Physical Widget (Logical Widget) Description udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) Represents the fields and occurrences of the entity as a multi-occurrence list. egrid (Grid) Represents the fields and occurrences of the entity within a grid framework, resembling a table. ucheckbox (CheckBox) Used to select one of two or three previously defined values. ucolorbox (ColorBox) Used to enter and display a standard color. ucolorlist (ColorList) Displays a list of system or Web colors. ucombobox (Combo Box) Used to select one item from a previously defined list, or enter user-defined data instead. ucmdbutton CommandButton Button that performs an action when clicked. By default, follows Windows look and feel. HeaderButton Button styled as a Windows column header. UnifaceButton Button that can be styled as desired using many properties unavailable with other logical button widgets. udragdrop DragSource Source for drag and drop behavior. DropTarget Target for drag and drop behavior. udropdownlist (DropDownList) Used to select one value from a list of alternative choices. ueditbox (EditBox) EditBox Input field used to enter, edit, and display text. NoEditBox Edit box for styling a field that displays text but does not allow editing. For compatibly purposes. Message Box Edit box for styling a field used to display a message. For compatibly purposes. ucontainer (FormContainer) Used to embed a form within another form. uhtml (HTML Widget) Renders HTML code (including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript) or displays a web page. uhyperlink (Hyperlink) Activates the detail trigger for the corresponding field. ulabel Label Displays text on a component, such as the name of an associated field or an instruction to the user. ulistbox (ListBox ) Displays an open list in which one or more values can be selected. umap (Map) Defines an area on an image that allows the user to interact by clicking on that area. umeter (Meter) Displays the value of a field by representing the value as the hand of a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values marked around the outer edge. (umonthcalendar) MonthCalendar Displays a calendar that allows the user to select a date. uOcxContainer (OcxContainer) Embeds OCXs in Uniface applications. uOleContainer (OleContainer) Embeds or defines links to OLE objects in Uniface applications. uoutputbox (OutputBox) Displays streaming text data, including unicode-encoded data. upicture (Picture) Displays an image. uprogressbar (ProgressBar) Shows the progress of a process or action that is being executed. uradiogroup (RadioGroup) Displays values as a set of mutually exclusive choices, each of which is displayed as a radio button. urtfeditbox (RichEditBox) Used to edit and store, including font and color attributes, as rich text format (RTF). uslider (Slider) Used to enter or modify a value by sliding an indicator in a set of a previously defined range of values. uspinbutton (SpinButton) Displays a numeric value that can be increased or decreased by a predefined interval within a predefined range. utab (Tab) Displays a tabbed container in which each tab contains a different form. utabex (TabEx) Displays a tabbed container in which each tab contains a different form. It is highly-customizable, allowing extensive control over the appearance and behavior of the tabs. utree (Tree) Hierarchically represents data; used for navigation through structured data. Related Links Widgets In Uniface, widgets are user interface controls. They can display data values, control how values are modified, and determine the appearance of those objects. Most widgets are field-level widgets. Logical Widgets Logical widgets are named configurations of physical widgets. A single physical widget may therefore have multiple logical widgets mapped to it. For fields, logical widgets provide the only way that physical widgets can be addressed. Properties for Styling the User Interface Each object that can be viewed in the user interface has a collection of properties that can be used to control what it looks like, and some other aspects of its visual behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}